summary: This document outlines a financial transaction involving J.P. Morgan and the establishment of new Special Purpose Vehicles (SPVs) to convert eligible unsecured assets into Asset-Backed Commercial Paper (ABCP). It details the structure of the ABCP issuance, including the roles of the Federal Reserve and various financial entities involved in the transaction.
keyFacts: J.P. Morgan is establishing five new SPVs to purchase eligible assets at amortized cost.
Series A ABCP (90%) will benefit from a liquidity backstop facility provided by the Federal Reserve.
Series B ABCP (10%) will be maturity matched against the assets purchased.
Eligible assets include short-term debt in the form of commercial paper or certificates of deposit.
The document mentions various financial entities and roles but does not specify named individuals.
